name: nullinside-site-monitor
description: A desktop application for keeping track of the status of the nullinside site and its microservices.

name: digital-wallet
description: A digital wallet microservices application written in typescript using kafka for communication between services along with saga distributated transaction pattern.

name: ECommerce
description: This project demonstrates an ECommerce application with three microservices: Order, Inventory, and Notification Services, using SQL Server and RabbitMQ, orchestrated with Docker Compose.

name: waste-sorting-app
description: A microservices-based backend application built for educating young people about waste sorting and promoting environmental awareness. This project is developed as part of an AMD Microservice course, utilizing Node.js, Express, MongoDB, and Docker to create a scalable and efficient architecture.

name: myEcomShop
description: A sample .NET microservices and container based application. Powered by .NET 9, C# 12, Docker, HybridCache, Redis, RabbitMq & Sql Server. Consists of two API projects, a Web frontend and a Queue processor.

name: message-queue-system-lld
description: Message Queue System A robust and scalable message queue application built using Java Spring Boot, designed to enable efficient asynchronous communication between microservices. This system provides reliable message delivery, fault tolerance, and support for high-concurrency environments.

name: event-ticketing-system
description: Event Ticketing System with Email Notifications - A Node.js backend application for managing event ticket sales, including user registration, event management, and ticket booking, with a microservice for email notifications using BullMQ. Built with TypeScript and PostgreSQL.

name: smart-logger-system-lld
description: A highly extensible and scalable logging system built with Java Spring Boot, implementing advanced design patterns such as Singleton, Strategy, Factory, and Chain of Responsibility. This application is designed to provide efficient logging, support dynamic log levels, and handle concurrency for high-throughput microservices.
